# Packaging manifest (issue #66).
#
# The web corpus explorer ships its BUILT Vue bundle (astrolyze/web/static/, declared as
# package-data in pyproject) but NEVER its frontend source tree or node deps. setuptools' build_py
# walker would otherwise sweep stray .py files out of node_modules/ (e.g. a bundled tool's
# python/ helper) into the wheel. `prune` is the reliable cross-environment exclusion the
# pyproject globs alone do not guarantee for node_modules. In CI the wheel is built from a fresh
# checkout with no node_modules, so this is primarily a local-build safeguard.
prune astrolyze/web/frontend
global-exclude */node_modules/*
